OL,3,CIs it the end of the road for lollipop
OL,4,Cpeople?
OL,6,F"We went to the Co-op and asked if we
OL,7,Fcould do a stall there. We had
OL,8,Fhundreds of people come along to sign
OL,9,FBilly's petition. But not only for
OL,10,FBilly, but for the other local
OL,11,Flollipop men and women whose jobs are
OL,12,Funder threat. We've got over a
OL,13,Fthousand signatures now.
OL,15,F"We love him, he's a part of the
OL,16,Fcommunity. Everyone loves Billy."
OL,18,FParis added: "Billy might lose his job
OL,19,Fand the roads are very busy. He's
OL,20,Fkeeping people safe and nobody would
OL,21,Fwant to lose him."
